  {
    "id": "ppg_npcc_hatchet",
    "name": "Hatchet",
    "role": "striker",
    "info": {
      "flavor": "<p>Nimble, clever, and borderline reckless, Hatchet mechs sport a variety of thrown weaponry and athletic enhancements. Detractors often claim that the Hatchet’s hit-and-run tactics are needlessly risky compared to conventional ranged weaponry. However, they often change their tune when a tree-sized, razor-sharp axe embeds itself inches from their cockpit.</p>",
      "tactics": "<p>Hatchet mechs are skirmishers, preparing a stinging <b><span style='font-variant: small-caps;'>Cleaving Retrieval</span></b> with a variety of hobbling <b><span style='font-variant: small-caps;'>Thrown</span></b> weapons. Once they retrieve their weapon, they use <b><span style='font-variant: small-caps;'>Flip Kick</span></b> to reset their position and restart pressure. <b><span style='font-variant: small-caps;'>Slowed</span></b> and <b><span style='font-variant: small-caps;'>Immobilized</span></b> hold their mobility in check.</p>"
